  "content_markdown": "Version: 8.2Sales EnterpriseSales Commerce\nOn this page\nIn Creatio invoices contain information about:\n* customer\n* supplier\n* connected contract\n* products in the order\n* order amount\n* payment conditions\nYou can create an invoice manually in the **Invoices** section or based on specific order. Invoices can be added both for all products of the order in their entirety and for specific steps of the installment plan based on payment.\nUse the **Invoices** section to work with invoices. The section includes multiple [quick filters](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=1017#title-1755-1).\n* By invoice issue date (the **Date** field of the invoice page). Displays invoices created within the specified period. To view the invoices created on a specific day, set the day as both the start and end date.\n* By status (the **Status** field of the invoice page). Displays invoices that have the specified status.\n* By owner (the **Owner** field of the invoice page). Displays invoices whose owner is the specified contact.\n## Create an invoice from the Invoices section\u200b\n1. **Open the Invoices section.**\n2. **Click New**. This opens the invoice page. Creatio generates invoice numbers automatically according to the \"Invoice number mask\" (\"InvoiceCodeMask\" code) [system setting](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=269).\n3. **Specify the customer** of the invoice in the **Contact** and **Account** required fields.\n4. **Select the Customer banking details** in the **Customer banking details** field. The field becomes editable when the customer account is selected.\n5. **Add the list of products and services** to pay using the current invoice. You can do this in multiple ways:\n1. Click ![btn_com_add_tab.png](https://academy.creatio.com/guides/sites/en/files/documentation/user/en/short_sales/BPMonlineHelp/short_sales_create_order/btn_com_add_tab.png) to open the product selection page.\n2. Click **New** at the bottom of the list.\nThe **Amount** field value includes the total cost of the ordered products and is calculated automatically. The amount can be specified in any currency. Learn more: [FAQ](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=2303).\nYou can **submit invoice for approval** to other Creatio users, for example, managers, using the out-of-the-box approval function. To do this, use the **Send for approval** button on the invoice page. The action opens an additional page where you set approval parameters. Learn more: [Approvals](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=1833).\nFig. 1 Send the invoice for approval\n![Fig.\u00a01 Send the invoice for approval](https://academy.creatio.com/docs/sites/academy_en/files/images/Composable_apps/Order_and_contract_management/scr_send_invoice_for_approval.png)\n## Create an invoice based on an order\u200b\n1. **Go to the Orders section and open the required record**.\n2. Click ![btn_actions.png](https://academy.creatio.com/docs/sites/academy_en/files/images/Composable_apps/Order_and_contract_management/btn_actions.png) \u2192 **Create new invoice** to **create an invoice based on the order** (Fig. 2).\nFig. 2 Add invoice based on order\n![Fig.\u00a02 Add invoice based on order](https://academy.creatio.com/docs/sites/academy_en/files/images/Composable_apps/Order_and_contract_management/scr_create_invoice_from_order.png)\n**As a result** , Creatio will open the invoice created based on the order. The invoice numbers are generated automatically according to the \"Invoice number mask\" (\"InvoiceCodeMask\" code) [system setting](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=269). The following data in the invoice is populated automatically using the order data:\n* The **Products** list.\n* The **Contact** , **Account** and **Owner** fields.\n* The **Amount** , **Amount, base currency** values.\n* The **Order** field.\nAlso, the **Start date** field is populated using the current date, the **Payment status** field will contain \"Draft\" and the **Supplier** field is populated using the \"Our company\" account type.\nIf necessary, you can generate a print-ready form of the invoice for the customer. To do this, click ![btn_print.png](https://academy.creatio.com/docs/sites/academy_en/files/images/Composable_apps/Order_and_contract_management/btn_print.png) and download the print-ready form. Additionally the form file is automatically saved in **Attachments** toggle panel.\n* * *\n## See also\u200b\n[Create a contract](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=1339)\n[FAQ](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=2303)",
